column325: I feel very neutral about the thought of watching television. I don't really enjoy watching lots of television.
probably it is going to be a relaxing time pass, with no concrete interest in watching television
I get excited at the thought of watching TV when it is a new program or a new episode that I am looking forward to.

When watching comedy, I get very happy during watching the television. But my joy won't last very long after watching it. However, when I watch something that's very sad, I can't help connecting my personal experience with the protagonist. The sadness usually last longer even after I stopped watching the show.
Mindless, a bit relaxed but feeling like I should be doing something else
I feel happy and relaxed. There is definitely no pressure or stress.
Usually good emotions.  I sometimes find myself getting really into a show.
Happiness, sleepiness if I watch TV late at night
It relaxes me and distresses me. It means I can take a break from other things or go to sleep
Watching television calms me down and relaxes me.
relaxing, a way to unwind after a long day
Excitement, fulfillment, entertainment. Watching TV usually increases my curiosity and gets me to think about things I normally wouldn't.
Watching T.V. makes me forget the rest of my day and allows me to be calm.
I think of TV shows, which makes me relaxed.
I would be excited to be able to relax and not really use my brain. It would depend what I'm watching. I would be excited if it was a show I liked.
For me, watching television usually puts me to sleep, so I'm surprised by this statement
It excites me and relaxes me.
Usually little interest or indifference. Could be doing something else
Happiness, Relaxation, happy to be doing nothing
Mostly relaxation; I watch TV when I have time to relax.
Happiness, relaxation, an escape from reality, I can breathe, joy, calm
I will feel sympathetic when bad things happens to the characters or the real people in the television. And sometimes i will feel physically hurt too.
